# Accordion

An accordion is a stacked list of items that, when clicked, reveal or hide related sections of content.
It puts customers in control of showing or hiding content.

It also help them organize information to keep screens less cluttered so that customers can accomplish tasks in short,
intuitive steps.

This component is one of the best ways to satisfy customers’ needs of control and simplicity,
which are sometimes conflicting requirements.

It’s also a key component in providing progressive disclosure,
showing customers just the right amount of content for that screen or step while allowing them to select additional content if they choose to.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/accordion
```

```tsx
import {
  Accordion,
  AccordionItem,
  AccordionItemHeader,
  AccordionItemBody,
} from '@ids-ts/accordion';
```

